      <hedline>
        <hl1>Swiss Tolerance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ewart Stuger letter praises Swiss voters for rejecting proposal to limit number of foreigners in country (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In rejecting a proposal to set a constitutional limit on the number of foreigners allowed in Switzerland (news article, Sept. 25), the Swiss have shown they can rise above the bigotry that is spreading across some countries in Europe.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In rejecting a proposal to set a constitutional limit on the number of foreigners allowed in Switzerland (news article, Sept. 25), the Swiss have shown they can rise above the bigotry that is spreading across some countries in Europe.</p>
        <p>This bit of soul-searching in a country with a sense of mission could slow the tide of immigrant-bashing. The vote could even turn out to be a defining moment in the country's attempt to be more tolerant of foreigners.</p>
        <p>EWART STUGER  Brooklyn, Sept. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
